FBIS3-34147 "drnes024_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-024 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Feb 1994 India Spokesman Questions Pakistan's Bhutto on UN Remarks BK0402083394 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0630 GMT 4 Feb 94 BK0402083394 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In Jammu and Kashmir, a government spokesman questioned the moral right of Pakistan Prime Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto to take up the issue of human rights in Kashmir. He said Pakistan sponsored militants are the main violators of human rights. He pointed out that since January 1990, these militants have killed as many as 2,300 innocent civilians -- mostly Kashmiri Muslims -- and abducted more than 1,000 people.
